  displayName: AlienPreviewPipeline
  description: Generate a Stage 1 structured scene description directly from the
    drawing.
  steps:
  - stepName: AlienPreview
    stepKind: 0
    llmProfile: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f40e4c6dcfeff664bb7f044018b3e88f, type: 2}
    userPromptTemplate: 'Describe everything visible in this drawing.

      Cover all figures, objects, actions, and spatial relationships. Include
      any notable elements beyond the main subjects — describe the full scene
      freely without anchoring to any particular element.

      Write preview_scene_reading so it can be presented as: "It looks like <scene>."

      ---

      For reference only — do not let this shape your description above.

      The player was asked to draw: {{target_objects}}

      After describing the scene, check whether Object A and Object B from
      that prompt are visible, unclear, or missing. Only mark visible when
      the drawing itself clearly supports it.'
    jsonMaxRetries: 3
    jsonRetryDelaySeconds: 0.1
    useVision: 1
    imageStateKey: reference_image
    requireImage: 1
    resizeLongestSide: 768
    customLinkTypeName: SampleCustomLink, Assembly-CSharp, Version=0.0.0.0, Culture=neutral,
      PublicKeyToken=null
    customAsset: {fileID: 0}
    customLinkParameters:
    - key: name
      value: 
    - key: title
      value: 
    - key: level
      value: 
